    <h1>Yum Yum Cooking</h1>
    <h2>Mo Buttu Mo Shuga Waffles</h2>
    <p>
      These waffles are incredibly delicious! The moment you start mixing the
      ingredients, the sweet aroma wafts through the kitchen, making you eager
      for them to be ready. With a perfect blend of flour, sugar, and a generous
      amount of butter, these waffles promise a delightful treat.
    </p>
    <p>
      As they cook, the outside becomes beautifully golden and crispy while the
      inside stays fluffy and soft. Each bite offers a rich, buttery flavor that
      is simply irresistible. Whether you enjoy them plain, with fresh berries,
      or drizzled with maple syrup, these waffles are sure to satisfy your
      cravings.
    </p>
    <p>
      Perfect for breakfast, brunch, or even a late-night snack, these waffles
      can easily become a favorite in your household. So gather your ingredients
      and treat yourself to this tasty delight—your taste buds will thank you!
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>2 cup all purpose flour</li>
      <li>3⁄4 cup sugar</li>
      <li>1 Tablespoon baking powder</li>
      <li>2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
      <li>1 3⁄4 cup milk</li>
      <li>2 eggs</li>
      <li>1 cup melted butter</li>
    </ul>

    <ol>
      <li>Mix flour, sugar, and baking powder in a large bowl.</li>

      <li>
        Separate egg yolks from whites and set the egg whites aside in a bowl.
      </li>

      <li>
        Next, mix in milk, egg yolks, vanilla, and butter into the bowl with the
        dry ingredients
      </li>

      <li>
        Beat egg whites for a few minutes in a mixer and fold into the batter.
      </li>

      <li>Cook waffles in a waffle iron for about 1-2 minutes</li>
    </ol>
  </body>
